    <text>
        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><add>Yiddish</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
          <p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Pa</placeName></p>
		<pb n="3"/>
			<p><add><hi rend="underline">Yiddish</hi></add></p> 
          <p rend="indent(10)"><placeName>N. Y.</placeName> <date>July 20&#44; 1849</date> <add>&#63;</add></p>
			<p>Honored Sir&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">Since I have not received a definite<lb/> answer from <placeName>Germany</placeName> about the Torahs&#44;<lb/> and you may not obtain everything just<lb/> as you wish it&#44; I permit myself to write<lb/> to you again. I assure you that this<lb/> copy is excellent and perfect&#44; in spite<lb/> of the fact that it is 28 inches long. The<lb/> writing in it is handsome and clear&#8212;not<lb/> too difficult. The columns are close to&#45;<lb/>gether&#44; so that it is not too heavy. I<lb/> shall also lower the price in view of<lb/> cash payment. Should you have no need<lb/> for it&#44; I beg of you to include the following<lb/> advertisement in the &#8220;Occident&#8221;&#58; Three<lb/> hundred and 60 catalogues will probably<lb/> arrive into your hands on <date>Wednesday</date><lb/> by express. If extraordinary circum&#45;<lb/>stances hinder me in this the matter<lb/> will rest &#39;till next month&#44; <del>for the follow&#45;</del><lb/> <persName>Frank&#39;s</persName> prayer book will not come up<lb/> to yours either in completeness or in<lb/> beauty or in translation&#44; but it will be<lb/> sold&#44; for our brothers for the most<lb/> part do not require all this. They<lb/> want a prayer book with English more<lb/> as a matter of vanity than as a matter<lb/> of necessity&#44; and they therefore buy</p>
			<p rend="Written in margin next to last 5 lines">Note this</p>
		<pb n="4"/>
			<p>the cheapest. With regard to <persName>Dr. Wort&#45;<lb/>mann&#39;s</persName> affair&#44; I received the enclosed.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">If several subscribers could be<lb/> obtained&#44; for your writings&#44; it could only<lb/> be for the <date>July</date> number and semi&#45;annual<lb/> subscriptions. More than &#36;1.50 could not<lb/> be obtained from anyone and that with<lb/> difficulty. I should have done it even<lb/> without your request.</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I hardly believe I shall be able to do<lb/> more for you. The fault is not mine.<lb/> That I tell you the truth&#44; you will soon<lb/> discover.</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)">Respectfully&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">Isidore Busch</persName></p>

          
        </body>
